          <blockquote>
              <p>I’m pretty sure all of this is done in NpcHandler. Within the method “AttackNPC” you should be able to create a death animation for NPCs using an if statement.</p>
<p><code>					if ((EnemyHP - hitDiff) &lt; 0) {
						hitDiff = EnemyHP;
					}
                                        if(npcs[NPCID].npcType == 9)
                                        npcs[NPCID].animNumber = 386;
                                        if(npcs[NPCID].npcType == 3200)
					npcs[NPCID].animNumber = 0x326; // drags: chaos ele emote ( YESSS ) 
                                        if(npcs[NPCID].npcType == 1605) {
					npcs[NPCID].animNumber = 386; // drags: abberant spector death ( YAY )
					} </code><br>
^ That’s in one of my sources.<br>
I’m not really sure for attacking and defending gfx atm.</p>
